revision.text:
{{Unsourced|date=September 2013}} The '''Arab National Council''' was an alliance of once warring Arabian tribes formed after the victorious uprising against nearly 400 years of [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] rule over Syria. [[T. E. Lawrence]] was instrumental in establishing this provisional Arab government under [[Faisal I of Iraq|King Faisal]], Lawrence had hoped to bring about independence from foreign colonialism by uniting the [[Arabs]]. Faisal's rule as king, however, came to an abrupt end in 1920, after the battle of [[Battle of Maysalun|Maysaloun]], when the French Forces of [[Henri Gouraud (French Army officer)|General Gouraud]], under the command of [[Mariano Goybet|General Mariano Goybet]], entered [[Damascus]], destroying Lawrence's dream of an independent Arabian rule over Syria; the council disbanded in the 1930s.
