{{Infobox company | name = Violent Lips, LLC | logo = VLLogo.JPG | logo_size = 200px | type = | foundation = 2011 | founders = Isabella Haddad, Sophia Haddad| location = [[Los Angeles, California]] | industry = [[Consumer goods]] | parent = | products = [[Cosmetics]] & [[Beauty]] | homepage = [http://www.violentlips.com/ www.violentlips.com] }}
'''Violent Lips''' is a cosmetics company founded by sisters Isabella and Sophia Haddad in 2011.<ref name="allure1">{{cite web|url=http://www.allure.com/beauty-trends/blogs/daily-beauty-reporter/2011/05/temporary-lip-tattoos-cool-or-just-plain-cuckoo.html |title=Temporary Lip Tattoos: Cool or Just Plain Cuckoo?: Daily Beauty Reporter: Daily Beauty Reporter |publisher=allure.com |date= |accessdate=2011-12-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.violentlips.com/pages/about-us |title=About Us |publisher=Violent Lips |date= |accessdate=2011-12-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111210151247/http://www.violentlips.com/pages/about-us |archive-date=2011-12-10 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> Their product line consists of [[temporary tattoo]] decals for the lips,<ref name="Micol Passariello">{{cite web|author=Micol Passariello |url=http://www.vogue.it/en/beauty/beauty-news-and-blogs/2011/05/temporary-lip-tattoos |title=Temporary Lip Tattoos |publisher=Vogue.it |date=2011-03-15 |accessdate=2011-12-09}}</ref> which create designs not possible with traditional [[lipstick]] - such as rainbows, animal prints, and polka dots.<ref name="cosmopolitan1">{{cite web|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/hairstyles-beauty/beauty-blog/temporary-lip-tattoos-051011#ixzz1OdqcoIE7 |title=Temporary Lip Tattoos - Review of Violent Lips Tattoos |publisher=Cosmopolitan |date=2011-05-10 |accessdate=2011-12-09}}</ref> At just 13 and 9 years old, the Haddad sisters were playing around with temporary tattoos. As a joke, they affixed them onto their lips and just like that the idea for temporary lip art was born.<ref name="allure.com">http://www.allure.com/beauty-trends/blogs/daily-beauty-reporter/2011/05/temporary-lip-tattoos-cool-or-just-plain-cuckoo.html</ref> The products have been featured by ''[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen]]'',<ref name="seventeen1">{{cite web|last=Magazine |first=Seventeen |url=http://www.seventeen.com/fashion/blog/kardashians-violent-lips?src=rss |title=Kardashian Beauty - Violent Lips |publisher=Seventeen |date=2011-11-18 |accessdate=2011-12-09}}</ref> ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'',<ref name="cosmopolitan1"/><ref name="cosmopolitan2">{{cite web|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/hairstyles-beauty/beauty-blog/khloe-kardashian-glitter-lips-picture-110311 |title=Khloe Kardashian Violent Lip Picture - Picture of Khloe Kardashian Lip Tattoo |publisher=Cosmopolitan |date=2011-11-03 |accessdate=2011-12-09}}</ref> ''[[Teen Vogue]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teenvogue.com/beauty/2011/10/halloween-beauty-products#slide=1 |title=Sally Hansen Limited Edition Salon Effects Nail Polish Strips: Halloween Beauty Products: Beauty |publisher=teenvogue.com |date= |accessdate=2011-12-09}}</ref> ''[[Vogue Italia]]'',<ref name="Micol Passariello"/> [[MTV|MTV Style]],<ref name="Style.mtv.com">{{cite web|url=http://style.mtv.com/2011/05/05/lip-tattoos/ |title=Let’s Discuss: Getting Your Lips Tatted Up Temporarily. Alarming Friends. Looking Awesome |publisher=Style.mtv.com |date= |accessdate=2011-12-09}}</ref> ''[[Elle Girl]]'',<ref>{{cite web|author=Aylin Ulutas |url=http://ellegirl.elle.com/teen-fashion/shopping-online/2011/fringe-trend-temporary-lip-tattoos/ |title=Fringe Trend: Temporary Lip Tattoos |publisher=Ellegirl.elle.com |date=2011-05-04 |accessdate=2011-12-09}}</ref> and ''[[Essence (magazine)|Essence]]''.<ref name="essence1">{{cite web|last=Margaret |first=Janell |url=http://www.essence.com/2011/05/18/go-there-wednesdays-temporary-lip-tattoo/#ixzz1OdqFK6nv |title=Black Beauty: Keyshia Cole Rocked Violent Lip Temporary Tattoos on '106 and Park' |publisher=Essence.com |date=2011-05-18 |accessdate=2011-12-09}}</ref> They have been worn by Khloé Kardashian, and her sisters Kendall and Kylie Jenner.<ref name="cosmopolitan2"/>
